## Module extensions

- `*.py,*.wsgi,*.js,*.jsx,*.ts,*.tsx,*.css,*.pcss,*.styl,*.md,*.json,*.yml,*.yaml,*.sh`

```shell
pip install setuptools virtualenv virtualenvwrapper-win

# Machine global:
mkvirtualenv PROJECT
workon PROJECT

# Project local:
python -m virtualenv .venv
python2 -m virtualenv -p C:\Python27\python.exe .venv
virtualenv .venv
.venv/bin/activate
call .venv/Scripts/activate

# Install all requirements:
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install flask
pip install Django==1.11.18
pip freeze django
pip freeze > requirements.txt
django-admin --version
python manage.py startapp testapp
```

Set variables:
```shell
WORKON_HOME=C:/Home/User/Envs
PYTHON_PATH=...
PATH=%PATH%;%PYTHON_PATH%;%PYTHON_PATH%/Scripts
VIRTUAL_ENV=.venv
```

NOTE: vim and python must be both 32 or 64 bit (32 bit on 2019.02.04 -- use 32bit Python27 -- python-2.7.15-32bit.msi)

